# Frontend Conventions

## UI Components (shadcn/ui)

- Prefer existing shadcn/ui components in `src/components/ui/` over custom markup.
- When adding a new component, read and follow `.agents/skills/shadcn/SKILL.md` (CLI, composition, styling, and forms rules).
- Use `bunx --bun shadcn@latest add <component>` from `apps/web/`.
- Compose with built-in variants (`variant`, `size`) and semantic tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`).

## Language

- All user-facing copy must be in **Simplified Chinese** (简体中文): page titles, descriptions, form labels, buttons, placeholders, validation messages, toasts, empty states, confirmations, and accessibility text (`aria-label`, `sr-only`).
- Brand names and proper nouns may stay as-is (e.g. `JX3`, `GitHub`).
- Code identifiers, route paths, and API field names stay in English; only rendered UI text is localized.

## Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS only. No separate CSS modules, styled-components, or inline styles for layout/theming.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` (or `#/lib/utils`) for conditional class names.

## Naming

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Page / route components | PascalCase file + export | `LoginComponent.tsx` |
| shadcn/ui primitives | lowercase (shadcn default) | `src/components/ui/button.tsx` |
| Routes | directory = URL path | `src/routes/login/index.tsx` → `/login` |
| Hooks, utils, API helpers | kebab-case | `use-user-query.ts`, `auth-client.ts` |

## Component Placement

Three tiers — pick the shallowest tier that fits:

| Tier | Location | When |
|------|----------|------|
| **Route-local** | `src/routes/<path>/-components/` | Used only by that route's page |
| **Shared among siblings** | Common parent route's `-components/` | Reused by multiple child routes under the same parent |
| **App-wide base** | `src/components/` (non-`ui/`) | Reusable across unrelated routes |
| **Primitives** | `src/components/ui/` | shadcn/ui and other design-system building blocks |

The `-components` prefix (leading `-`) excludes the folder from the URL. Colocate schemas and hooks with the components that use them inside the same `-components/` directory when they are not shared.

Example — login page with private form pieces:

```
src/routes/login/
  index.tsx                              # route entry, thin
  -components/
    LoginComponent.tsx                   # container (API / mutations)
    AuthCredentialsFormComponent.tsx     # presentational form
    auth-credentials-schema.ts           # zod schema
```

Example — settings area shared by child routes:

```
src/routes/settings/
  -components/
    SettingsLayoutComponent.tsx          # shared by /settings/* children
  profile/
    index.tsx
  security/
    index.tsx
```

Do **not** put route-specific components in `src/features/` or top-level `src/components/`.

## Forms: Two-Layer Pattern

Every form feature splits into **container** (API) and **presentational** (render + validation) components. Both live in the route's `-components/` directory (or a shared parent `-components/` when reused).

- **Inner (`*FormComponent`)**: renders fields, runs client-side validation (zod), exposes `onSubmit` with validated data. No API calls.
- **Outer (`*Component`, e.g. `LoginComponent`)**: wires React Query mutations/queries, handles loading/error/success, passes callbacks and initial values to the form component.

Do not mix API logic and form rendering in a single component.

## Data Fetching (TanStack Query)

- Use `@tanstack/react-query` for all client-side API calls (`useQuery`, `useMutation`, `useQueryClient`).
- Colocate query keys and fetch functions in kebab-case modules under `src/lib/` (see `web-lib-structure.mdc` for folder layout) or next to the consuming `-components/`.
- Admin resource APIs live in `src/lib/api/admin/`; shared fetch helpers live in `src/lib/api/request.ts` — do not duplicate `requestJson` or `ApiRequestError` per resource.
- Invalidate or update cache after mutations instead of manual refetch scattered in components.
- Use route `loader`s for SSR-critical initial data; use React Query for interactive refetching and mutations.

## TanStack Start — Routing

- **Always use directory structure as the URL path.** One folder per route segment; the folder name becomes the URL segment (e.g. `routes/login/index.tsx` → `/login`, `routes/users/$id/index.tsx` → `/users/:id`).
- **Root `/` exception:** the home URL has no path segment, so use a single `routes/index.tsx` file (not `routes/index/index.tsx`, which would map to `/index/`).
- Route entry file: `index.tsx` inside the route folder for non-root routes.
- Do **not** use flat route files like `routes/login.tsx` when a directory route is intended.
- Keep route `index.tsx` thin: define the route, optionally a loader, then render a PascalCase page component from `-components/`.
- Pathless / non-URL folders use a leading `-` prefix (e.g. `-components/`).
- Use `#/*` path alias for cross-cutting imports (`#/lib/...`); prefer relative imports within the same route's `-components/`.
- Auth and API proxy routes stay under `src/routes/api/`; business API calls target the backend via the existing proxy pattern.
- Follow [TanStack Start docs](https://tanstack.com/start) for SSR, server functions, and router integration.

## Structure

```
src/
  components/ui/           # shadcn / design-system primitives
  components/              # app-wide reusable base components (rare)
  lib/                     # domain subfolders — see web-lib-structure.mdc
    api/                   # request helpers, proxies, admin resource APIs
    auth/                  # client, guards, session
    query/                 # query client
    utils/                 # cn, formatters
    logging/               # isomorphic logger
  routes/
    __root.tsx
    index.tsx              # / (root — no directory segment in URL)
    login/
      index.tsx            # /login
      -components/         # login-only components
    api/                   # server / proxy routes
```
